items.name: Anko Mitarashi - Naruto
items.description:
I saw a disturbing lack of Anko. So this is to remedy that. A good part of it is from Naruhodou. So support him if you can he is a great artist.

The LORA came out rather stable crapping out at .95. You may want to set it as .55 or .6 for a more balanced style otherwise it looks too much like naruhodou's art. Seems to have some propensity to add more than one Anko, probably some contamination from the model. It that an error? is that a feature? Anyway the solo tag seems to fix that

I experimented with her dango(the candy she likes to eat) but YMMV with that, the LORA seems to wants to use them as jewellery some times.

Had good results with: <lora:AnkoMitarashi:0.55>, AnkoMitarashi, solo, big_breasts, AnkoCoat, AnkoFishnet, microskirt, covered_nipples

Covered nipples seems to work better than simple nipples otherwise they may poke out of her mesh.

I tried to englobe her attire as following(so you can try to mix and match):

  1. AnkoCoat

  2. AnkoFishnet

  3. microskirt

Tried to train her cursed seal but could find almost no images plus it is on the back of her neck, I tagged it as Ten_no_Juin.

Anyway I have added the tag summary inside the dataset so you can experiment.

items.name: Pavolia Reine (Hololive ID)
items.description:
LoRA model for Pavolia Reine from Hololive Indonesia.

All pictures, comments and reviews are appreciated as I can't test all the usage scenarios.

Weight around 0.8-1 but feel free to play around.

For v2b :

Main triggers:

  • pavolia reine (all training pictures contains it so it's a main trigger that you can work with)

  • reine-long-hair

  • reine-short-hair

  • reine-main-outfit

  • reine-second-outfit

Full triggers that focuses on specific part :

  • reine-long-hair, very long hair, side ponytail, braided bangs, feather hair ornament, white pupils, single earring,

  • reine-short-hair, short hair, braided bangs, feather hair ornament, white pupils, earrings

  • reine-main-outfit, blue dress, dress, detached sleeves, navel cutout, white thighhighs

  • reine-second-outfit, black collared shirt, crop top, white pants, midriff, bare shoulders

Most of the time no need to use full prompts, often using "pavolia reine, long hair" or "reine-short-hair, short hair" i enough, just experiment around.

(You might want to use long dress instead of blue dress at times)

Additional triggers :

  • shawl

  • blue eyes, green eyes or teal eyes (depends if you need it)

  • grey hair (for low CFG or stubborn LoRA/checkpoints)

Issues I have encountered and some workarounds :

  • Mixing short hair with her main outfit is unstable and stubborn.

    Outfit have problems with correctly generating at times or second outfit bleeds over.

    Increasing CFG to 9 or a bit higher helps with that. Adding crop top and black sleeveless shirt to negatives helps with bleeding.

    Using only "pavolia reine, short hair and main outfit triggers" also helps with main outfit generation.

  • Main outfit bleeds to outfits that have focus on breasts area when using long hair triggers, especially problematic with dress related outfits and armours

    Reducing CFG to 5 and increasing weight of specific outfit helps a bit (might need to be up to 1.5 or so...)

    Also adding dress, blue dress to negatives helps a lot.

    (At times it can create creative outfits as armour stylized after her dress)

    (Weirdly enough not many issues with bikini and similar???)

    That problem is less common or not existent when using short hair.

  • Other LoRA do work well depending on their quality.

NSFW capable without problems.

Hope you will enjoy it!

items.name: Contact - Style
items.description:
What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on a particular style. It is an illustration style more oriented to western cartoons.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my customs: https://civitai.com/models/24149 and https://civitai.com/models/26332)

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA.

The LoRA works well on NSFW (check last examples).

The images are created using different weights (you can check on the image generation panel)

Different Flavors

My LoRAs are usually trained on AI generated images in two different steps. The first training uses images generated using a model (I choose it based on what I'm going to build) with a size of 512x768, and this is usually 10 images with different content but a similar style. The second training is based on pictures generated using the LoRA from the first step. This is done at a higher resolution (768x1152) and the output is usually upscaled using img2img.

The LoRA is available in two different flavors:

  • RAW: This is based on the first batch of images, it has usually a more creative output, but usually needs hiresfix or img2img to really shine

items.name: INDIGO
items.description:
INDIGO was created to be capable of realistic images of excessively large breasts, wildly inventive scenarios, and stylized beauty. The result is something that lies somewhere between top digital fetish art and an actual photograph.

It excels at creating realistic depth and texture with little effort, and creating massive breasts (or hyperbreasts, as some may know them) on realistic-looking people. Inpainting works great, and it plays well with many LoRAs.

Official Page: https://www.mesmerizersgaming.com/free-gallery/stable-diffusion-models/

UPDATE: JUNE 21 2023

Safetensors is now uploaded! The description has been updated with recommended prompt words.

Prompting

These guidelines will help you create similar images to the ones in the examples.

Structure

I break down the prompt into 3 main parts:

  1. Head – [Style of image], [Main description], [Anatomy Descriptions]

  2. Body – [Porn Websites/Companies], [Style descriptions], [Photography terms]

  3. Tail – [Minute/repetitive details]

Anything in the Body of the prompt can be shifted elsewhere within the Body if the image needs a stronger/weaker emphasis on it.

Positive

[Style of image], [Main description], [Anatomy Descriptions], [Porn Websites/Companies], [Style descriptions], [Photography terms], [Minute/repetitive details]

Negative

[Style of image], [Anatomy Descriptions], [Style descriptions], [Photography terms], [Minute/repetitive details]

Weighting

For positive prompts, lightly weight any words that you feel like you can afford to lessen the impact on. Because of this, you will draw more attention to the rest of the prompt without having to risk weighting something you want too heavily.

For negative prompts, lightly weight all the words you use, then after some test generations you can scale any individual weights up as necessary.

Breast Prompting

  • big supple boobs

  • huge hyperbreasts (may get cartoonish)

  • huge wide tits (may create thiccer women)

  • tight [type of clothing]

  • breast expansion (also great for BE: sideboob, underboob)

  • breast inflation (only if breast expansion prompts are not working, may introduce latex and/or balloons. also useful: ripped top)

General Prompting

  • [your favorite porn websites or companies] (experiment with what works for you, be mindful of how these images are used)

  • skin texture, high resolution, sharp focus, depth of field, dynamic range, bokeh

  • pinup

  • goosebumps, stretch marks, freckles (at end of Tail and weighted lightly. helps make more realistic people)

Face Prompting

  • stunning eyes (creates beautiful, quality eyes. may ‘overwrite’ other eye descriptions.)

  • round face, high cheek bones (include these in the Tail of the prompt. The goal is filtering images closely linked with traditional beauty standards, and not necessarily the traits themselves)

Negative Prompting

  • manga, cartoon, cgi (weighted heavily, will push image further into realism)

  • beads (weighted heavily. can help make the nipples look more natural, and stave off extra nipples.)

  • extra limbs

  • missing limb

  • fused together

  • duplicate, couple, group (if multiple people in the image are not desired. usually not needed unless generating images larger than 1024px)

  • elongated, twisted (also not usually needed unless the aspect ratio is rather wide)

Recommended Settings

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Step Count: 20

  • CFG: 7.5

items.name: Irina Jelavić (Assassination Classroom)
items.description:
Irina Jelavić from Assassination Classroom trained on 42 SFW and NSFW images. Make sure to read everything because there's a few... quirks with this lora you'll want to know about.

Use irina jelavic to generate Professor Bitch. For her full outfit, use:

  • black choker

  • white jacket

  • black sleeveless shirt

  • white skirt

  • black belt

  • high heels

I also included as many images of her in her bikini as I could find (which isn't many) and managed to get surprisingly consistent results for it as well. It's not perfect, but a lot better than I was expecting:

  • black choker

  • irinabikini

Since there's very few fanart images of her, most of the images I used were taken from the anime itself which I think ended up influencing the style of the lora. I tagged all the anime images with anime screencap so you can try putting that in the negative prompts to see if it improves anything. Besides that here are a couple other things:

  • when generating her in her normal outfit, I recommend adding bra, black bra, flower in the negative prompts

  • she's wearing a choker in 95% of the images in the dataset and while I haven't had too much issue generating her without it, you might want to put choker, black choker in the negative prompt if you don't want it

If anyone has any images of her you think I probably missed (fanart, not from the anime - I already have more than enough of that), feel free to post them in the comments or send them to me via Discord (GuileGaze#4436). I want to make a v2 with a better dataset to iron out the kinks, but it can be tedious finding quality images for training.

items.name: Perfect Sketchbook 完美草图
items.description:
Made this on complete accident. I think this serves as a practical exercise in what applying a huge amount of lineart style LoRAs to a model until it's almost ruined and then replacing unet blocks IN06, IN07, IN08, OUT05, OUT4, and OUT3 with that of realistic model does.

This model creates a sort of sketchbook like effect to the model. You've got the bones of a semi-realistic model as far as anatomy goes but it looks like someone drew it in with pencil. I call it Perfect Sketch, because basically you can throw any prompt you'd use on Perfect World in here and it'll work.

I can do a more detailed explanation of why this works if anyone's interested but if you're only interested in prompting here are the usage recommendations.

Usage

Ideally you should prompt for realism for best effects. With SketchyAnimeStyle it doesn't really matter, but with SketchStyle it will help a lot. If you don't want to come up with your own prompt, just insert this before your prompt.

(ultra high detail, realistic, best quality, 8k raw, masterpiece)

BREAK

As far as negatives go, keep it simple. Once again, if you don't want to come up with your own prompt, I generally like to use this.

easynegative, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (monochrome:1.1), watermark

Don't use latent upscaler and if you upscale at 2 or below keep the denoise at 0.4 or below.

With SketchyStyle you should use a upscaler otherwise the facial details will not resolve. With SketchyAnimeStyle it doesn't really matter that much though obviously upscaling is better.

Process

Huggingface

Generally speaking, anything between OU03toOUT5/IN8toIN6 is responsible for segmenting the face and body. I was trying to correct anatomy breakdown after fucking up the weights with loras so I replaced the parts of the unet responsible for compressing and uncompressing the body features with those of the functioning model I started with. This enforces the anatomy of that model into this one to some degree while leaving the fine details intact. I think this could be used as a generalized approach, where you can apply loras to change style and then revert certain blocks to restore anatomy or aesthetic composition. However, this technique is largely experimental and needs more research.

We have completely revamped the model merge hierarchy for endlessMix. This time, we have prepared three models:

  • v2.0RA: A model that is similar to the middle ground between V2A and V2R.

  • v2.0A: A model that is biased towards anime illustrations. It works well with prompts like cute, kawaii, chibi, and loli.
